theorem interior_closure_eq_self_of_open
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (hA : IsOpen (A : Set X)) :
    interior (closure (A : Set X)) = A := by
  classical
  -- We prove the two inclusions separately, then use `Subset.antisymm`.
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · -- `interior (closure A) ⊆ A`
    intro x hxInt
    by_contra hxNotA
    -- From `hxInt` we know `x ∈ closure A`.
    have hxCl : x ∈ closure (A : Set X) :=
      (interior_subset : interior (closure (A : Set X)) ⊆ closure A) hxInt
    -- Consider the open set `V = interior (closure A) \ A` that contains `x`.
    have hOpenInt : IsOpen (interior (closure (A : Set X))) := isOpen_interior
    have hVOpen  : IsOpen (interior (closure (A : Set X)) \ A) :=
      hOpenInt.diff hA
    have hxV : x ∈ (interior (closure (A : Set X)) \ A) :=
      ⟨hxInt, hxNotA⟩
    -- Since `x ∈ closure A`, every neighbourhood of `x` meets `A`.
    -- In particular, `V` meets `A`, yielding a contradiction.
    have hNonempty :
        ((interior (closure (A : Set X)) \ A) ∩ A : Set X).Nonempty :=
      (mem_closure_iff).1 hxCl _ hVOpen hxV
    rcases hNonempty with ⟨y, ⟨⟨_, hyNotA⟩, hyA⟩⟩
    exact hyNotA hyA
  · -- `A ⊆ interior (closure A)`
    exact
      interior_maximal
        (subset_closure : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure A) hA

theorem IsOpen.diff {α : Type*} [TopologicalSpace α] {U V : Set α}
    (hU : IsOpen (U : Set α)) (hV : IsClosed (V : Set α)) :
    IsOpen (U \ V : Set α) := by
  have hOpenComplV : IsOpen (Vᶜ : Set α) := by
    simpa using hV.isOpen_compl
  simpa [Set.diff_eq] using hU.inter hOpenComplV
